  "title": "Is Latin America starting to retreat from early and universal childbearing?",
  "abstract": "The 2000 censuses show that the proportion of women below age 30 who are mothers has dropped substantially in most Latin America countries, suggesting that the social imperative of early motherhood, which has long prevailed in the region, is weakening.",
